\series bold 
Objective 
\layout Standard

To explore the phenomenon of uniform circular motion and the acceleration
 needed to maintain it.
\layout Standard


\series bold 
Overview
\series default 
 
\layout Standard

You have recently studied projectile motion.
 In this unit we are going to explore another phenomenon in two dimensions,
 uniform circular motion.
 In particular, you will develop a mathematical description of the centripetal
 acceleration that keeps an object moving in a circle.
 You will start by watching a toy "airplane" suspended from a string fly
 in a circle.
